avdta.network

Class ReadNetwork

  • java.lang.Object
    • avdta.network.ReadNetwork
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReadDemandNetwork

    public class ReadNetwork
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains methods to read network and transit data for AVDTA. To use this class, see readNetwork(avdta.project.Project).

      • readNetwork

        public Simulator readNetwork(Project project)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a Simulator corresponding to the data contained with the specified project. If the project is a TransitProject, transit vehicles will be added.
        Parameters:
        project - the project
        Returns:
        the Simulator for the project
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if a file cannot be accessed

      • createTransit

        public void createTransit(TransitProject project)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Creates transit vehicles and writes them to the bus file. The number of vehicles created depends on the routes in the bus_period and bus_frequency files. This overwrites the bus file.
        Parameters:
        project - the project
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if a file cannot be accessed

      • readTransit

        public void readTransit(TransitProject project)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        Reads created transit vehicles from the bus file and assigns them to the appropriate paths. This method also initializes BusLinks for mode choice models using transit. If there are no transit vehicles, see createTransit(avdta.project.TransitProject).
        Parameters:
        project - the project
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if a file cannot be accessed

      • createZones

        public Zone[] createZones(int id,
                          Location loc)
        Creates zones for the specified id and location. The destination zone uses -id.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the zone
        loc - the location
        Returns:
        returns an array containing the created zones in the order (origin, dest).

      • readLinks

        public java.util.Set<Link> readLinks(Project project)
                              throws java.io.IOException
        Reads in all links from the links file. For links with a TransitLane, two separate links will be created (the TransitLane and the main link). TransitLanes do not appear separately in the links file.
        Parameters:
        project - the project
        Returns:
        a set of all Links
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if a file cannot be accessed

      • readPhases

        public void readPhases(Project project)
                throws java.io.IOException
        Reads signal phases and signal cycle offsets from the phases and signals files. Signal data will be ignored if the node it is assigned to is does not have a Signalized.
        Parameters:
        project - the project
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if a file cannot be accessed
